Sen. JD Vance’s elevation as former President Donald Trump’s vice presidential running mate did tremendous work to elevate awareness of him among the American electorate, especially among the former president’s 2020 base.&nbsp;
According to Morning Consult’s latest surveys, Vance — who came into the vice presidential nod subject to equal levels of favorable and unfavorable opinions among voters — saw nearly identical growth in opinions on both sides of the ledger, while the share who said they’d never heard of him fell from 35% to 13%.
